<BLIST><TITLE><CODEROUTINE>Graphics2D</CODEROUTINE>'s attributes can be set with:</TITLE>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>setStroke</CODEROUTINE><BR/>
<BLIST><TITLE><CODEROUTINE>BasicStroke</CODEROUTINE> holds information about:</TITLE>
  <ITEM><CODEROUTINE>line width</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
  <ITEM><BLIST><TITLE><CODEROUTINE>join style</CODEROUTINE></TITLE>
    <ITEM><CODEROUTINE>JOIN_BEVEL</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
    <ITEM><CODEROUTINE>JOIN_MITER</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
    <ITEM><CODEROUTINE>JOIN_ROUND</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
  </BLIST></ITEM>
  <ITEM><BLIST><TITLE><CODEROUTINE>end-cap style</CODEROUTINE></TITLE>
    <ITEM><CODEROUTINE>CAP_BUTT</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
    <ITEM><CODEROUTINE>CAP_ROUND</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
    <ITEM><CODEROUTINE>CAP_SQUARE</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
  </BLIST></ITEM>
  <ITEM><CODEROUTINE>dash style</CODEROUTINE></ITEM></BLIST>
</ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>setPaint</CODEROUTINE><BR/>
<BLIST><TITLE>The <CODEROUTINE>Paint</CODEROUTINE> has three implementations</TITLE>
  <ITEM><CODEROUTINE>Color</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
  <ITEM><CODEROUTINE>GradientPaint</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
  <ITEM><CODEROUTINE>TexturePaint</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
</BLIST>
</ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>setComposite</CODEROUTINE><BR/>
<BLIST><TITLE><CODEROUTINE>AlphaComposite</CODEROUTINE></TITLE>
    <ITEM><CODEROUTINE>SRC_OVER</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
    <ITEM><CODEROUTINE>SRC_IN</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
    <ITEM><CODEROUTINE>SRC_OVER</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
    <ITEM><CODEROUTINE>DST_OVER</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
    <ITEM><CODEROUTINE>DST_IN</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
    <ITEM><CODEROUTINE>DST_OVER</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
    <ITEM><CODEROUTINE>CLEAR</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
</BLIST></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>setTransform</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>setClip</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>setFont</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>setRenderingHints</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
</BLIST>
<CODEROUTINE>Graphics2D</CODEROUTINE> holds references to its attribute objects--they are not cloned. If you alter an attribute object that is part of the <CODEROUTINE>Graphics2D</CODEROUTINE> context, you need to call the appropriate set method to notify the context. Modifying an attribute object during rendering causes unpredictable behavior.<BR/>
<BLIST><TITLE><CODEROUTINE>Graphics2D</CODEROUTINE>'s rendering methods:</TITLE>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>draw</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>fill</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>drawString</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>drawImage</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
</BLIST>
<BLIST><TITLE><CODEROUTINE>Graphics2D</CODEROUTINE>'s transformation methods:</TITLE>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>rotate</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>scale</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>shear</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>translate</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>transform</CODEROUTINE><BR/>
<BLIST><TITLE><CODEROUTINE>AffineTransform</CODEROUTINE> has some helpers factory methods:</TITLE>
  <ITEM><CODEROUTINE>getRotateInstance</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
  <ITEM><CODEROUTINE>getScaleInstance</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
  <ITEM><CODEROUTINE>getShearInstance</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
  <ITEM><CODEROUTINE>getTranslateInstance</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
</BLIST></ITEM>
</BLIST>
<BR/><BR/><BR/>
<BLIST><TITLE>Classes in <CODEROUTINE>java.awt.geom</CODEROUTINE></TITLE>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>Arc2D</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>Ellipse2D</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>QuadCurve2D</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>Area</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>GeneralPath</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>Rectangle2D</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>CubicCurve2D</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>Line2D</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>RectangularShape</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>Dimension2D</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>Point2D</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>RoundRectangle2D</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
</BLIST>
Float and double-precision implementations of each of the geometries are provided as inner classes.
<BR/><BR/><BR/>
<BLIST><TITLE><CODEROUTINE>Area</CODEROUTINE> is a special type of <CODEROUTINE>Shape</CODEROUTINE> that supports boolean operations:</TITLE>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>add</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>subtract</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>intersect</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
<ITEM><CODEROUTINE>exclusiveOr</CODEROUTINE></ITEM>
</BLIST>
<BR/><BR/><BR/>
